WEBVTT

00:01.251 --> 00:04.254
♪ mysterious music playing ♪

00:08.717 --> 00:11.720
♪ theme song playing ♪

00:37.079 --> 00:40.749
♪

00:40.749 --> 00:42.000
[whooshing, pop]
[grunts]

00:42.709 --> 00:44.211
[whooshing, pop]
[grunts]

00:44.837 --> 00:48.298
[whooshing, pop]
[Leela screaming]

00:48.298 --> 00:50.843
[dogs barking]
[Nibbler grunting, panting]

00:52.135 --> 00:54.388
- [sniffing]
- Is your dog friendly

00:54.388 --> 00:56.640
- or just ugly?
- Very friendly!

00:56.640 --> 00:57.808
[Nibbler growls]
[dog yelps]

00:57.808 --> 01:00.352
But, he's not a dog.
[slurps]

01:00.352 --> 01:03.689
I am gonna sue you
for every last-- Ah!

01:03.689 --> 01:04.690
[slurping]

01:04.690 --> 01:05.941
[muffled]
<i>Pursuant to--</i>

01:05.941 --> 01:07.943
[slurping]

01:08.694 --> 01:09.778
Good dog.

01:09.778 --> 01:11.613
♪

01:11.613 --> 01:14.700
<i>Tonight's winning number
was approximately six.</i>

01:14.700 --> 01:16.618
[Nibbler babbling]

01:16.618 --> 01:18.036
[panting, grunting]

01:18.036 --> 01:19.037
[loud blast]

01:19.037 --> 01:21.748
Don't most pets eat at home
and poop outside,

01:21.748 --> 01:23.125
like college students?

01:23.125 --> 01:24.877
Nibbler prefers his litter box.

01:24.877 --> 01:27.588
It contains precious sand
with essential minerals

01:27.588 --> 01:29.089
from his home world.

01:29.089 --> 01:31.008
[sparkling]
Plus, it's got nose-numbing crystals.

01:31.008 --> 01:33.552
So, <i>that's</i> why you never clean it!

01:33.552 --> 01:35.053
Uh, right.

01:35.053 --> 01:37.181
And speaking of changing the subject,

01:37.181 --> 01:39.641
who wants to see
the new alien language movie

01:39.641 --> 01:41.185
by Bax Glygglif?

01:41.185 --> 01:42.728
I heard it's brilliant!

01:42.728 --> 01:44.980
Ah, sorry. I don't do subtitles.

01:44.980 --> 01:46.106
When I go to the movies,

01:46.106 --> 01:48.317
I don't wanna have to
look up from my phone.

01:48.901 --> 01:50.903
I'd like to see the film, Leela.

01:50.903 --> 01:53.071
Nibbler! You can talk!

01:53.071 --> 01:55.449
You always forget I can talk.

01:55.824 --> 01:57.951
Nibbler! You can talk!

01:57.951 --> 02:00.954
♪ dramatic music playing ♪

02:00.954 --> 02:02.956
[rumbling]

02:02.956 --> 02:04.791
[alien screeching]

02:04.791 --> 02:06.793
[audience crying]

02:06.793 --> 02:08.212
[alien screeching]

02:08.212 --> 02:10.047
[audience laughing]

02:11.089 --> 02:12.883
What a romantic movie!

02:12.883 --> 02:15.427
My heart just melted when Dupdup said...

02:15.427 --> 02:16.887
[both screech]

02:16.887 --> 02:18.514
[both laughing]

02:18.514 --> 02:21.767
Although I wasn't crazy
about that big floating head.

02:21.767 --> 02:23.810
It was the best thing in the movie!

02:23.810 --> 02:27.064
No, no. The one in front of me,
blocking my view.

02:27.481 --> 02:28.690
[slurps]

02:28.690 --> 02:30.442
♪

02:30.442 --> 02:31.902
[beeping]

02:33.111 --> 02:35.197
What's a 2x3x5 letter name

02:35.197 --> 02:38.200
for a 3x23x29 number name

02:38.200 --> 02:41.620
for a movie featuring a 1x4x9 object?

02:41.620 --> 02:42.621
Easy.

02:42.621 --> 02:45.207
<i>2001: A Space Odyssey.</i>

02:45.207 --> 02:46.542
Aha!

02:46.542 --> 02:49.419
[game beeping]

02:49.419 --> 02:50.921
[whirring]

02:50.921 --> 02:53.674
Nibbler, you really are my BFF.

02:53.674 --> 02:56.385
My best furry friend.
[grunting]

02:56.385 --> 02:58.053
[stomach rumbling]
Too corny?

02:58.053 --> 03:00.389
[grunting, retchs]

03:00.389 --> 03:02.182
Merely a hairball. I'm perfectly--

03:02.182 --> 03:03.892
[retching, groaning]

03:03.892 --> 03:04.893
[thud]

03:04.893 --> 03:07.104
Uh, let's get that looked at.

03:07.104 --> 03:10.107
♪

03:10.107 --> 03:11.608
[grunting]

03:11.608 --> 03:13.986
Well, he seems to have
eaten this endoscope.

03:13.986 --> 03:15.821
But also, he's got worms.

03:15.821 --> 03:17.489
Worms? That's all?

03:17.489 --> 03:20.242
No. That's not all.
Let me finish speaking for once.

03:20.242 --> 03:22.119
The worms are attacking his brain.

03:22.119 --> 03:25.706
Without treatment,
he'll be left with the IQ of a terrier.

03:26.123 --> 03:27.708
A <i>Boston</i> terrier.

03:27.708 --> 03:29.585
- No!
<i>- Mon Dieu!</i>

03:29.585 --> 03:31.003
Fortunately, there's a cure.

03:31.003 --> 03:33.005
What is it-- Sorry.

03:33.005 --> 03:34.464
Ivermectin.

03:34.464 --> 03:36.508
It's a powerful dewormer, okay?

03:36.508 --> 03:39.928
Now, if you're done <i>interrupting</i>,
we're finished.

03:39.928 --> 03:42.139
- Thank you--
- I! Wasn't! Finished!

03:42.139 --> 03:45.434
♪

03:45.434 --> 03:47.394
Just one pill every three hours.

03:47.394 --> 03:49.188
Come on. Open wide.

03:49.188 --> 03:51.231
[stubborn growling]

03:51.231 --> 03:53.734
He won't listen. His brain's going.

03:53.734 --> 03:56.403
My mom always hid my medicine
in something yummy.

03:56.403 --> 03:59.072
- Like paste.
- That's sad and dumb.

03:59.072 --> 04:00.574
How about cheese?

04:00.574 --> 04:01.658
Yes! Cheese!

04:01.658 --> 04:03.535
Maybe Gouda. Or a nice brie!

04:03.535 --> 04:05.537
[excited growling]

04:06.914 --> 04:09.833
[chomps, happy humming]

04:09.833 --> 04:13.253
♪

04:13.253 --> 04:16.507
How's that medicine working?
You up for a game of Quantum Wordle?

04:16.507 --> 04:19.968
Um, how about something
more deterministic,

04:19.968 --> 04:21.553
like tic-tac-toe?

04:21.553 --> 04:23.514
Tic-tac-toe?
FRY: Ooh!

04:23.514 --> 04:26.558
I love that game!
You know, there's a trick to winning.

04:26.558 --> 04:28.393
[whispers]
<i>Always be X.</i>

04:28.393 --> 04:29.937
Would you like to play?

04:29.937 --> 04:31.438
Sure! I'll be O.

04:32.606 --> 04:35.734
You need more medicine, Nibbler.
Want some Manchego?

04:35.734 --> 04:36.944
Make it American.

04:36.944 --> 04:39.446
In individual plastic-wrapped slices.

04:39.446 --> 04:40.864
- ♪ dramatic sting ♪
- No!

04:40.864 --> 04:42.741
Leela, what's happening to me?

04:42.741 --> 04:46.203
I've been taking all my pills
like a good boy, yet still, I...

04:46.203 --> 04:48.455
I feel my smartness slipping away.

04:48.455 --> 04:50.958
I don't know, little Fuzzler.

04:51.834 --> 04:55.587
♪ melodramatic music playing ♪

04:55.587 --> 04:58.090
[sniffling]

04:58.090 --> 05:01.009
Sad news, everyone.

05:01.009 --> 05:03.011
Oh good, you're already crying.

05:03.011 --> 05:05.931
Nibbler's medicine is killing
the worms in his body,

05:05.931 --> 05:09.101
but they've also infested
the litter box itself.

05:09.101 --> 05:12.563
They reinfect him every time he uses it.

05:12.563 --> 05:15.023
- Then throw out the litter.
- No!

05:15.023 --> 05:16.316
He needs it to live!

05:16.316 --> 05:18.485
It's from his ancestral pooping grounds.

05:18.485 --> 05:20.112
Isn't there some other way?

05:20.112 --> 05:21.405
Only one.

05:21.405 --> 05:24.116
But, fortunately, it's dead simple.

05:24.116 --> 05:27.160
You must shrink down
and battle the worms...

05:27.160 --> 05:29.162
face-to-face!

05:29.872 --> 05:31.915
Really? That sounds gross.

05:31.915 --> 05:33.292
Oh my, yes.

05:33.292 --> 05:34.251
And dangerous.

05:34.251 --> 05:35.836
Oh my, yes!

05:35.836 --> 05:37.504
At least it's dead simple.

05:37.504 --> 05:39.047
That's where you're wrong!

05:39.047 --> 05:41.508
♪ dramatic sting ♪
Remember my enlarging ray?

05:41.508 --> 05:43.135
CREW:
No.

05:43.135 --> 05:46.555
By reversing the lens,
it becomes an all-new kind of ray

05:46.555 --> 05:48.807
that keeps things the same size.

05:50.392 --> 05:52.477
Then, with just a few minor adjustments...

05:52.477 --> 05:54.146
[beeping]
<i>Voilà!</i>

05:54.146 --> 05:55.731
Shrinking ray!

05:55.731 --> 05:59.026
[ray blasts, ship whirring]

05:59.526 --> 06:01.820
[growling]

06:03.363 --> 06:06.116
Once you're in, you'll kill the worms

06:06.116 --> 06:09.244
with high-powered rifles
loaded with deadly rounds

06:09.244 --> 06:11.163
of liquid ivermectin.

06:11.163 --> 06:13.332
And you'll travel in this toy tank

06:13.332 --> 06:15.584
I enlarged with my enlarging ray.

06:15.584 --> 06:17.961
[impressed murmuring]
BENDER: Neat.

06:17.961 --> 06:19.838
- And this track?
- Track?

06:19.838 --> 06:22.341
Oh, right!
It came with the set.

06:22.341 --> 06:25.636
Everybody in.
Enjoy the carnage!

06:26.220 --> 06:28.180
[Fry and Leela grunting]

06:28.180 --> 06:29.473
[cover creaks, slams]

06:29.473 --> 06:30.807
Amy, shove it!

06:30.807 --> 06:32.559
No! <i>You</i> shove it!

06:32.559 --> 06:33.852
Oh. You mean this thing.

06:33.852 --> 06:35.646
[grunting]

06:35.646 --> 06:37.898
♪ adventurous music playing ♪

06:37.898 --> 06:39.149
[all yelling]

06:40.150 --> 06:42.319
[ray blasting]

06:43.570 --> 06:44.821
[whirring]

06:44.821 --> 06:46.406
Whoopsie-doops!

06:46.406 --> 06:48.742
[blasting, whirring]

06:49.368 --> 06:51.495
[gasps] My Manwich!

06:51.495 --> 06:53.497
[crew yelling]

06:53.497 --> 06:54.748
[whirring]

06:54.748 --> 06:56.458
Go, baby, go!

06:56.458 --> 06:57.876
[crew yelling]

06:57.876 --> 06:58.627
[beep]

06:58.627 --> 07:00.045
[fire whooshing]

07:00.045 --> 07:01.129
[yelling]

07:01.129 --> 07:03.465
♪ dramatic crescendo ♪

07:03.465 --> 07:04.967
[quiet thud]

07:05.759 --> 07:09.096
[on radio]
<i>Whatever you do, don't leave the tank.</i>

07:09.096 --> 07:10.848
<i>It's your only protection</i>

07:10.848 --> 07:13.767
<i>against the brutal desert conditions.</i>

07:13.767 --> 07:17.563
[sand shifting]
[crew screaming]

07:18.021 --> 07:19.439
<i>And no screaming!</i>

07:20.440 --> 07:23.318
♪ tense music playing ♪

07:23.318 --> 07:25.696
[wind blowing]

07:26.989 --> 07:30.284
[all coughing, spitting]

07:30.284 --> 07:31.785
[squeaking]

07:31.785 --> 07:33.078
[clang]

07:33.078 --> 07:35.330
[wind blowing]

07:35.330 --> 07:39.001
Poor Nibbler is counting on us
to find those worms,

07:39.001 --> 07:40.919
no matter how grueling the hunt.

07:40.919 --> 07:42.921
Then, we'll need litter box food.

07:42.921 --> 07:45.841
Maybe we can eat those
weird pygmy hyena moles.

07:46.341 --> 07:48.427
[chomp]
Ow!

07:48.427 --> 07:49.928
[cackling]

07:49.928 --> 07:52.681
♪ mystical music playing ♪

07:52.681 --> 07:54.391
Orange sparklies?

07:54.391 --> 07:56.852
Zoidberg's going to bedazzle his lungs!

07:56.852 --> 07:59.104
[inhales]

07:59.605 --> 08:01.523
♪ dramatic crescendo ♪

08:01.523 --> 08:04.985
♪ psychedelic music playing ♪

08:04.985 --> 08:07.237
[echoing]
<i>Zoidberg? Are you okay?</i>

08:07.237 --> 08:10.115
- They're coming, why not.
- Who's coming?

08:10.115 --> 08:12.201
I don't know. Maybe those guys?

08:12.201 --> 08:14.369
♪ tense music playing ♪

08:14.369 --> 08:16.371
[rumbling]

08:16.371 --> 08:18.373
[scuttling]

08:23.420 --> 08:24.421
♪

08:24.421 --> 08:26.006
[all groaning]

08:26.840 --> 08:28.467
Stop, or we'll shoot!

08:29.551 --> 08:33.013
Ugh! Blech! They're attacking!
Prepare to fire!

08:33.013 --> 08:34.598
[guns cocking]
FRY: Hang on a sec!

08:34.598 --> 08:36.600
I'm taking a whiz.
[urinating]

08:36.600 --> 08:38.894
At least <i>one</i> of you has manners.

08:38.894 --> 08:41.772
I thank you for your gift of moisture.

08:41.772 --> 08:45.067
- No problem!
- We've come in search of parasitic worms,

08:45.067 --> 08:48.028
so we can slaughter them violently.
Are you them?

08:48.028 --> 08:49.279
Alas, no.

08:49.279 --> 08:51.573
The sandworms are our enemies, too.

08:51.573 --> 08:53.283
<i>We</i> are beetles.

08:53.283 --> 08:56.078
Ah, of course. Dung beetles.

08:56.078 --> 08:58.497
It is pronounced <i>Doong.</i>

08:58.497 --> 09:00.165
The G is almost silent.

09:00.165 --> 09:03.126
Welcome to the world of Doon...

09:03.126 --> 09:04.127
g.

09:04.127 --> 09:07.589
The ancient prophecy
speaks of a messiah.

09:07.589 --> 09:10.634
Could he be the Kwiznos Cadillach?

09:10.634 --> 09:13.345
♪ dramatic music playing ♪

09:15.848 --> 09:17.224
Nope.

09:17.224 --> 09:21.019
The sun grows hot,
and my deodorant grows weak.

09:21.019 --> 09:24.982
Please, join us in the Hall of Doong.

09:24.982 --> 09:27.276
I'm gonna try those big meatballs.

09:27.276 --> 09:29.611
♪ tense music playing ♪

09:32.364 --> 09:34.283
Can I offer anyone some spit?

09:34.283 --> 09:35.993
We have flat and sparkling.

09:35.993 --> 09:37.703
I will have two of each.

09:37.703 --> 09:38.620
[spitting]

09:39.121 --> 09:41.999
The sandworms you seek roam the desert,

09:41.999 --> 09:44.626
devouring all in their path.

09:46.628 --> 09:50.132
Behold! A map of the universe.

09:50.132 --> 09:51.800
[snickering]

09:51.800 --> 09:55.220
The worms congregate here,
by the great sphere.

09:55.220 --> 09:57.139
But your journey will be treacherous,

09:57.139 --> 10:00.767
for virtually all paths end in death.
[beeping]

10:00.767 --> 10:02.895
Then let's just take the shortest one.

10:02.895 --> 10:04.855
To help you navigate safely,

10:04.855 --> 10:07.524
<i>I</i> must use the glitter chamber,

10:07.524 --> 10:11.236
which allows me to see
all realities at once.

10:11.236 --> 10:13.322
I won't lie, it's pretty cool.

10:13.322 --> 10:15.616
That's what Zoidberg snorted.

10:15.616 --> 10:17.201
Does that make <i>me</i> cool?

10:17.201 --> 10:18.619
Absolutely not!

10:18.619 --> 10:21.121
Only shamans may use the sacred chamber.

10:21.121 --> 10:25.459
For anyone else,
it could induce a medical-grade freakout!

10:25.459 --> 10:26.752
Like Narlo here.

10:27.753 --> 10:30.839
Dude, I feel like I'm spinning...

10:32.508 --> 10:34.009
[sparkling]

10:34.009 --> 10:36.637
♪ mystical music playing ♪

10:38.430 --> 10:41.308
♪ mystical vocalizing ♪

10:41.308 --> 10:43.644
- [device beeping]
- Has anyone seen my--

10:44.269 --> 10:45.562
Oh!

10:45.562 --> 10:47.773
[snarling]
Aha!

10:47.773 --> 10:49.274
Give me that slipper!

10:49.274 --> 10:50.359
Drop it!

10:50.359 --> 10:51.360
Whoa! Oh!

10:53.654 --> 10:54.947
It's ruined!

10:54.947 --> 10:56.198
Bad Nibbler!

10:56.198 --> 10:58.075
[gasps] I can't help it!

10:58.075 --> 10:59.535
[howling]

10:59.535 --> 11:01.912
It's those damnable worms!

11:01.912 --> 11:04.289
There, there. I know what might help.

11:04.289 --> 11:05.624
No! No, I beg of you!

11:05.624 --> 11:06.917
Not the cone of shame!

11:07.835 --> 11:09.294
♪ somber music playing ♪

11:09.294 --> 11:10.754
[quiet crying]

11:10.754 --> 11:12.756
♪ intense music playing ♪

11:12.756 --> 11:15.759
♪ mystical vocalizing ♪

11:15.759 --> 11:17.177
[sparkling]

11:18.470 --> 11:20.722
I see the way.

11:20.722 --> 11:23.225
And I have a serious craving for frosting.

11:24.351 --> 11:27.354
[slurping]

11:28.647 --> 11:30.232
Mm... [slurps]

11:30.232 --> 11:32.693
Make a right at the large sand mound,

11:32.693 --> 11:35.112
then a left at the medium-sized mound.

11:35.112 --> 11:37.656
After the fifth mound,
you'll see a mound.

11:37.656 --> 11:39.575
So many mounds!

11:39.575 --> 11:42.411
One wrong mound means certain death.

11:42.411 --> 11:44.371
Or just take the roach-thopter.

11:44.371 --> 11:47.374
[wings fluttering]

11:47.374 --> 11:48.917
Bleh!

11:48.917 --> 11:51.253
Then, you'll need a guide. Bilgar!

11:52.504 --> 11:54.756
Bilgar is our second-best guide.

11:54.756 --> 11:57.426
Our best guide got eaten by a sandworm.

11:57.426 --> 11:59.344
Listen to him closely,

11:59.344 --> 12:01.972
and do <i>most</i> of what he says.

12:01.972 --> 12:04.975
♪ exotic music playing ♪

12:09.354 --> 12:11.773
The worms are attracted
to the rhythmic pattern

12:11.773 --> 12:13.609
of Doong beetle footsteps.

12:13.609 --> 12:16.862
Whatever you do,
do not walk like a Doong beetle.

12:17.946 --> 12:20.199
Oops!
[clicking, whirring]

12:21.909 --> 12:24.912
♪ exotic music continues ♪

12:25.829 --> 12:28.332
Even in this hostile environment,

12:28.332 --> 12:30.125
life thrives.

12:30.125 --> 12:32.628
For example, the veiny pus fungus.

12:32.628 --> 12:34.546
[disgusted groans]

12:34.546 --> 12:36.673
And the hairless sand pigeon.

12:36.673 --> 12:38.300
[louder groans]

12:38.300 --> 12:41.762
Every living creature here
is a total barf bag!

12:41.762 --> 12:43.722
Uh, n-no offense, Bilgar.

12:43.722 --> 12:46.099
These little crawly guys are cute.

12:46.099 --> 12:47.643
Hello, friends.

12:47.643 --> 12:49.436
[scuttling]
[Fry and Leela gag]

12:49.436 --> 12:51.396
BENDER:
That's the worst one of all!

12:51.396 --> 12:54.399
♪ exotic music continues ♪

12:56.985 --> 13:00.989
This final expanse is where
our best guide was devoured.

13:02.407 --> 13:03.784
[flame sizzles]

13:03.784 --> 13:05.410
So, what do we do?

13:05.410 --> 13:07.496
Exactly what he did.

13:07.496 --> 13:10.290
I'll create a diversion
by setting off a pounder.

13:11.875 --> 13:14.002
[rhythmic pounding]

13:14.002 --> 13:16.463
Hey, you know my grandfather
was a pounder.

13:16.463 --> 13:19.758
It simulates beetle footsteps
to attract the worms.

13:19.758 --> 13:20.884
Go, run!

13:20.884 --> 13:22.719
[panting]
[Zoidberg whooping]

13:22.719 --> 13:24.096
Don't worry about me.

13:24.096 --> 13:26.265
Our best guy taught me everything he--

13:26.265 --> 13:28.225
[screaming]
[sandworm bellows]

13:28.225 --> 13:29.810
[Bilgar screaming]

13:29.810 --> 13:33.188
Hey, I guess that makes me
a quarter-pounder.

13:33.188 --> 13:35.274
[sandworm bellowing, roaring]

13:35.274 --> 13:37.276
[all screaming]

13:39.278 --> 13:42.614
♪ adventurous music playing ♪

13:42.614 --> 13:44.575
[all panting]

13:44.575 --> 13:47.286
[all exclaiming]

13:48.328 --> 13:49.705
LEELA: Oh!

13:49.705 --> 13:51.748
Fry, why don't you have a belt?

13:51.748 --> 13:53.876
Or at least a substantial butt!?

13:53.876 --> 13:56.128
Sorry, guys, I'm a flatty.

13:56.128 --> 13:57.504
[all screaming]

13:58.505 --> 14:00.299
[sparkling]

14:00.299 --> 14:02.342
Oh, right. Sand.

14:02.342 --> 14:04.845
♪ mystical music playing ♪

14:04.845 --> 14:07.139
Hey! Don't bogart that glitter!

14:07.848 --> 14:09.808
- It's coming.
- What's coming?

14:09.808 --> 14:12.561
- A tasty wienerschnitzel?
- A funny monkey?

14:12.561 --> 14:14.188
Sandstorm!

14:14.188 --> 14:16.607
[wind howling]
[all yelling]

14:16.607 --> 14:19.026
[grunting]

14:19.026 --> 14:21.028
[wind howling]
[coughing, groaning]

14:21.028 --> 14:23.405
It's hopeless!
We don't have a guide!

14:23.405 --> 14:25.032
We don't know where we are!

14:25.032 --> 14:27.284
The dust is drying out my skin!

14:27.284 --> 14:28.619
[clang] Ow!

14:28.619 --> 14:31.163
[vibrating]

14:31.163 --> 14:32.164
[clang]

14:32.164 --> 14:34.416
♪ epic music playing ♪

14:34.416 --> 14:36.668
LEELA:
The sphere! We made it!

14:36.668 --> 14:38.086
Great work, Bender!

14:38.086 --> 14:40.214
This is it. Arm squirt guns!

14:40.214 --> 14:41.757
[plastic pumping]

14:41.757 --> 14:44.676
But we lost that poundy thing
that attracts the worms.

14:44.676 --> 14:47.262
Ah, but we have Tappy and Shoe-shoe!

14:47.262 --> 14:49.806
They call me the two-ton Fred Astaire.

14:49.806 --> 14:51.850
[rattling, squeaking]
Yep. Yep.

14:55.395 --> 14:56.480
The jitterbug?

14:56.480 --> 14:57.648
The litter bug!

14:58.315 --> 15:00.067
He's a dancing machine!

15:00.776 --> 15:02.402
[grunts, sighs]

15:02.402 --> 15:03.487
[clapping]

15:03.487 --> 15:05.531
[loud rumbling]

15:05.531 --> 15:07.824
[growling, snarling]

15:07.824 --> 15:10.452
Set squirties to kill!

15:10.452 --> 15:12.788
[snarling]

15:17.543 --> 15:20.128
- [Bender and Leela gasp]
- It's worms within worms!

15:20.128 --> 15:21.505
[thudding]

15:22.881 --> 15:26.718
[squeaky voice]
I am the God Emperor of Doon...g.

15:26.718 --> 15:30.180
It's them! The parasites that
are making Nibbler stupid!

15:30.180 --> 15:33.809
I know you. You're those worms
that used to live in my tum-tum.

15:33.809 --> 15:35.769
Only you made <i>me</i> smarter.

15:35.769 --> 15:37.604
I'll take your word for it.

15:37.604 --> 15:40.440
Look, you seem like
a nice swarm of maggots,

15:40.440 --> 15:42.943
but you're making my friend Nibbler sick.

15:42.943 --> 15:45.028
Can't you just infest Zoidberg?

15:45.028 --> 15:47.489
Ew! We prefer to live free,

15:47.489 --> 15:49.449
here among the tumble-turds.

15:49.449 --> 15:52.578
Then prepare for me to say fire. Fire!

15:52.578 --> 15:54.079
[worm yelps]

15:54.079 --> 15:56.498
That was my second-best guard!

15:56.498 --> 15:59.251
Worms, form a defensive squiggle!

15:59.251 --> 16:01.503
[worms shouting]

16:01.503 --> 16:02.754
[both yell]

16:04.798 --> 16:07.426
♪ adventurous music playing ♪

16:07.426 --> 16:08.927
Oh...

16:14.975 --> 16:16.476
[Bender laughing]

16:16.476 --> 16:20.439
[worm yelping, grunting]

16:21.023 --> 16:22.274
FRY:
Good job...

16:22.274 --> 16:23.150
knot!

16:24.401 --> 16:26.111
[Fry laughs]
[worms screaming]

16:26.111 --> 16:28.155
♪ music swells ♪

16:28.155 --> 16:29.865
[panting]

16:29.865 --> 16:31.867
[sniffing]

16:32.826 --> 16:34.077
♪ dramatic music playing ♪

16:34.077 --> 16:36.205
Whoa...

16:37.039 --> 16:38.999
Look! Up in the sky!

16:38.999 --> 16:40.959
- It's a bird!
- It's a turd!

16:40.959 --> 16:42.669
It's Nibbler!

16:46.173 --> 16:48.967
- [beep]
- Stop! Stop fighting!

16:48.967 --> 16:51.470
♪

16:51.470 --> 16:53.347
Okay, I'm done.

16:53.347 --> 16:55.224
Nibbler? Are you alright?

16:55.224 --> 16:57.684
How dumb are you on a scale of one to Fry?

16:57.684 --> 17:00.354
I can't even count that high anymore.

17:00.354 --> 17:01.772
But please listen.

17:01.772 --> 17:05.442
I have important things to say,
while I still can.

17:05.442 --> 17:06.944
[wind blowing]

17:06.944 --> 17:08.946
[wings fluttering]

17:08.946 --> 17:11.448
♪

17:13.075 --> 17:15.786
♪ mystical vocalizing ♪

17:15.786 --> 17:18.205
It is he! The Messiah!

17:18.205 --> 17:20.791
As pictured in the ancient scripture.

17:20.791 --> 17:23.085
It shows him with blonde hair
and blue eyes,

17:23.085 --> 17:25.045
but the rest is spot on.

17:25.045 --> 17:27.506
I only wish I had more time left

17:27.506 --> 17:30.425
to appreciate this glittering litter land.

17:30.425 --> 17:33.303
Everywhere I look, I see beauty.

17:33.303 --> 17:35.138
Really? 'Cause I'm seeing poop.

17:35.138 --> 17:37.891
Open your minds and see as I see.

17:37.891 --> 17:41.395
All life is connected in a glorious web.
[sparkling]

17:42.271 --> 17:45.315
<i>The pus fungus draws life from the dust</i>

17:45.315 --> 17:47.526
<i>and is eaten by the skin pigeon,</i>

17:47.526 --> 17:51.196
<i>which in turn feeds the pygmy hyena mole.</i>

17:51.196 --> 17:54.449
- [chomp]
- Ow... That's cool.

17:54.449 --> 17:56.577
NIBBLER:
The beetles process the dung--

17:56.577 --> 17:59.162
It's pronounced <i>doong.</i>

17:59.162 --> 18:01.415
Uh, sorry, Messiah. Keep going.

18:01.415 --> 18:03.208
As for the worms...
[sparkling]

18:03.208 --> 18:06.378
<i>well, they feed on my brain.</i>

18:06.378 --> 18:08.505
<i>And that in itself is blutier--</i>

18:08.505 --> 18:10.883
<i>Um, uh, boo-too-poo-pool.</i>

18:10.883 --> 18:12.551
[stammering]

18:12.551 --> 18:14.136
<i>Pretty.</i>

18:14.136 --> 18:16.180
Everything is interconnected.

18:16.180 --> 18:18.140
Everything is perfect.

18:18.140 --> 18:21.476
So please, leave these worms
to play their part,

18:21.476 --> 18:22.895
and I...

18:22.895 --> 18:25.439
I will happily play mine,

18:25.439 --> 18:28.859
even if it means sacrificing all that I am

18:28.859 --> 18:31.570
and becoming a mindless house pet.

18:31.570 --> 18:33.405
[crying]

18:33.405 --> 18:34.781
[slurping]

18:34.781 --> 18:37.618
I accept your gift of precious liquid.

18:37.618 --> 18:39.995
Finally, you learn some manners.

18:40.996 --> 18:43.498
♪

18:44.625 --> 18:46.460
[Nibbler's craft whirring]

18:46.460 --> 18:48.587
[ray blasts, ship whirs]

18:50.172 --> 18:52.341
[pop]
[all exclaim]

18:53.133 --> 18:54.968
[Nibbler whimpers]

18:54.968 --> 18:57.095
One last 3D crossword

18:57.095 --> 18:59.181
before your brain turns to jello?

18:59.181 --> 19:03.018
Alas, my mind has already
degenerated to the point

19:03.018 --> 19:04.978
where I can no longer predict the ending

19:04.978 --> 19:07.314
of an M. Night Shyamalan movie.

19:07.314 --> 19:08.398
[all gasp]

19:08.398 --> 19:11.360
[sobs] B-But you're my little Fuzzler.

19:11.360 --> 19:14.947
When all else is gone,
I shall remember that.

19:14.947 --> 19:16.532
Oh, Nibbler!

19:16.532 --> 19:18.575
I know you've made your mind up,

19:18.575 --> 19:20.285
o-or what's left of it,

19:20.285 --> 19:24.248
but please don't let the worms
eat your consciousness!

19:24.623 --> 19:26.959
Now, now, my cherished friend.

19:26.959 --> 19:28.627
Though my mental,

19:28.627 --> 19:31.171
uh, brain may deteriorate,

19:31.171 --> 19:34.675
I will always look back
on what we had with...

19:34.675 --> 19:35.759
big happy.

19:36.260 --> 19:38.887
And you is... be my buddy and...

19:39.763 --> 19:42.266
so, so...

19:42.266 --> 19:43.350
itchy.

19:43.350 --> 19:45.644
[whimpering]

19:45.644 --> 19:48.063
Leela, give belly rub.

19:48.063 --> 19:50.732
[cooing]

19:50.732 --> 19:53.986
[sobbing]

19:53.986 --> 19:56.280
♪ somber music playing ♪

19:56.280 --> 19:58.407
[crying, sniffles]

19:58.407 --> 20:01.869
Aw, Leela, I hate seeing you like this.

20:01.869 --> 20:04.413
You wanna blow your nose on my shirt?

20:04.413 --> 20:05.914
[blows nose]

20:06.540 --> 20:07.875
Thanks, Fry.

20:07.875 --> 20:09.751
I know this is what Nibbler wanted,

20:09.751 --> 20:11.795
but I can't wrap my head around it.

20:11.795 --> 20:14.631
If only I could open my mind to the beauty

20:14.631 --> 20:16.842
he was blabbering on about.

20:16.842 --> 20:17.718
[gasps]

20:17.718 --> 20:20.304
[ray blast, whirring]

20:20.304 --> 20:23.307
♪ dramatic music playing ♪

20:23.307 --> 20:25.976
[engines roaring]

20:28.187 --> 20:32.191
Please. The chamber is my only hope
of truly understanding!

20:32.191 --> 20:34.318
Well, then find another only hope.

20:34.318 --> 20:37.196
Pure, uncut glitter is dangerous.

20:37.196 --> 20:39.364
You could end up
permanently tasting colors.

20:39.364 --> 20:40.991
Or smelling sounds.

20:40.991 --> 20:42.284
I can smell sound.

20:42.284 --> 20:44.578
Fry's singing stinks up
the whole apartment.

20:44.578 --> 20:47.331
Yeah! And if you don't let Leela
use the chamber,

20:47.331 --> 20:49.416
I'm gonna stink up this whole place.

20:49.750 --> 20:52.920
<i>♪ I feel a song coming on! ♪</i>

20:52.920 --> 20:54.213
[retching]

20:54.213 --> 20:56.548
Fine! Go nuts.

20:58.967 --> 21:01.970
[whooshing, sparkling]

21:01.970 --> 21:04.056
♪ mystical music playing ♪

21:04.056 --> 21:07.059
♪ mystical vocalizing ♪

21:10.729 --> 21:13.899
[young beetles giggling]

21:13.899 --> 21:15.400
[whooshing, sparkling]

21:17.486 --> 21:19.154
I see the way.

21:19.154 --> 21:21.114
[coughing]

21:21.657 --> 21:23.825
Everything Nibbler said was true.

21:23.825 --> 21:26.036
Duh. He's the Messiah.

21:26.036 --> 21:28.038
But he did miss one thing.

21:28.038 --> 21:30.749
He works in mysterious ways.

21:31.416 --> 21:34.753
These parasitic worms should be
making Nibbler smarter,

21:34.753 --> 21:36.171
like when Fry had them.

21:36.171 --> 21:37.798
So why aren't we?

21:37.798 --> 21:40.259
Because the web of life
extends even deeper

21:40.259 --> 21:42.010
than Nibbler perceived.

21:42.010 --> 21:44.096
You worms have been weakened

21:44.096 --> 21:45.848
by sub-parasites!

21:45.848 --> 21:47.349
♪ dramatic sting ♪
[scuttling]

21:47.349 --> 21:48.934
[disgusted groans]

21:48.934 --> 21:50.727
Oh, that is gross, man!

21:50.727 --> 21:54.022
These tiny mites are sapping
your beneficial juices.

21:54.022 --> 21:56.567
[loudly]
<i>I have been a little low-energy lately!</i>

21:56.567 --> 21:58.026
[scuttling]

21:58.026 --> 22:01.405
[slurps] I'm feeding on
worm juice with friends!

22:01.405 --> 22:02.739
That's it! I'm out!

22:02.739 --> 22:05.450
Sorry I didn't mention
I was shrinking myself.

22:05.450 --> 22:07.119
You guys must have been worried sick.

22:07.744 --> 22:09.037
[Fry clears throat]

22:10.372 --> 22:14.042
There are levels
within levels within levels.

22:14.042 --> 22:15.752
That's too many levels!

22:15.752 --> 22:18.046
We've gotta kill those mites!

22:18.046 --> 22:21.508
What!? But what about the precious web
of blah-biddy-blah?

22:21.508 --> 22:23.427
You have to draw the line somewhere.

22:23.427 --> 22:25.929
Stomp those suckers!
Kill 'em all!

22:25.929 --> 22:27.514
[panicked yelling]

22:27.514 --> 22:29.683
[grunting]

22:29.683 --> 22:32.853
♪ dramatic music playing ♪

22:32.853 --> 22:34.563
It's showtime!

22:36.106 --> 22:37.566
Care to smoosh?

22:40.235 --> 22:42.654
[shoes tapping]

22:42.654 --> 22:45.240
Bender, stop! It's me, Zoidberg!

22:45.240 --> 22:48.368
Sorry! I can't hear your screams
over the tapping!

22:48.368 --> 22:49.536
[groaning, grunts]

22:50.245 --> 22:51.288
Dah!

22:54.625 --> 22:56.460
[toy squeaking]
[Nibbler grumbling]

22:57.294 --> 22:59.087
You're gonna be okay.

22:59.087 --> 23:00.631
But what about you, Leela?

23:00.631 --> 23:03.091
You were in that
dangerous glitter chamber.

23:03.091 --> 23:05.344
[echoing]
<i>Did your senses get scrambled?</i>

23:05.344 --> 23:07.012
Nah, it's fine.

23:07.012 --> 23:10.641
The interwoven dependency of all things

23:10.641 --> 23:12.684
was the ultimate epiphany.

23:12.684 --> 23:15.312
Yet, thanks to Leela's unwavering loyalty

23:15.312 --> 23:17.022
and utmost bravery,

23:17.022 --> 23:20.984
my consciousness returned to
ponder another glorious phase

23:20.984 --> 23:23.695
of our universe's evolution.

23:24.488 --> 23:26.281
<i>Good.</i>

23:26.281 --> 23:28.700
[chattering]

23:28.700 --> 23:30.869
[sniffles] You're my little Fuzzler.

23:30.869 --> 23:32.663
I remember.

23:32.663 --> 23:35.666
[purring]

23:35.666 --> 23:38.877
♪ gentle music playing ♪

23:41.922 --> 23:44.925
♪
